Daily Guide to Miracles from Oral Roberts Ministries
Love: the Antidote for Hate — by Oral Roberts
When someone hurts us, the first reaction of our flesh is to feel
anger, resentment, and hatred toward that person and want to get
even. And all too often, we do not seek to overcome those feelings
through forgiveness. We allow hate, like a spider, to spin its web
around our souls.
Whenever an insect becomes entangled in a spider's web, the spider
immediately attacks the insect, filling its body with poison. Then
the spider strengthens the web, making death certain.
Hate is like the spider. It fills the soul with toxins, setting off a
chemical reaction in the body, poisoning the bloodstream and
imprisoning the spirit. Worse, such hatred is in direct opposition to
Jesus' teaching. He said, Love your enemies, bless them that curse
you, do good to them that hate you, and pray for them which
despitefully use you, and persecute you. (Matthew 5:44)
Love is the only antidote for hate. One way to activate love against
hate is to remember that Christ died for the hateful person the same
as He died for you. That person is also made in the image of God and
carries a divine imprint upon his or her soul. In hating them, you
are also hating God. Activating God's love in your spirit destroys
both the web and spider of hate, cleansing your being of the poison
and setting you free.
Henry Ford once said, &quot;I shall never let anyone drag me down by
making me hate him.&quot; That's a good motto to live by.
My Declaration of Faith for Today: I forgive those who wrong me and
walk in love toward them, knowing that God loves them as He loves me.
Remember, &quot;Something GOOD is going to happen to you!&quot;
