Quoted
Christ is full and sufficient for all his people. He is bread, wine, milk, living waters, to feed them; he is a garment of righteousness to cover and adorn them; a Physician to heal them; a Counselor to advise them; a Captain to defend them; a Prince to rule; a Prophet to teach; a Priest to make atonement for them; a Husband to protect; a Father to provide; a Brother to relieve; a Foundation to support; a Root to quicken; a Head to guide; a Treasure to enrich; a Sun to enlighten; and a Fountain to cleanse. JOHN SPENCER (1630–1693)
Today's Verses - KJV
1 Th 2:13-16 For this cause also thank we God without ceasing, because, when ye received the word of God which ye heard of us, ye received it not as the word of men, but as it is in truth, the word of God, which effectually worketh also in you that believe. For ye, brethren, became followers of the churches of God which in Judaea are in Christ Jesus: for ye also have suffered like things of your own countrymen, even as they have of the Jews: Who both killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets, and have persecuted us; and they please not God, and are contrary to all men: Forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles that they might be saved, to fill up their sins alway: for the wrath is come upon them to the uttermost.
My Comments
When we hear the Word of God; how do we take it? Do we take it as being the Word of God or just what someone says? When we quote what the Word of God says about a thing we have had some say &quot;I don't believe it that way&quot;! Do they realize they are saying they know more about it than God! This kind of thinking will never make it into the kingdom of God. This kind of thinking is at the root of why there are so many different denominations that all claim to know God but are not living according to His Word. As it was with the early church so it is now, in this generation. The early church was persecuted because of the gospel of Christ; told as it is. It still happens today. Those who preach repentance, abstinence from sin are being called legalists and narrow minded, holy rollers, etc. Some are even calling it hate speech! Beloved, Christ is not one of many ways to approach God, He is the only way! This makes some very angry with us. So be it, it happened to all who came before us and it will happen to us as well! People in churches, all over the world, are being told they are eternally saved who have never repented of their sins and are still doing things that the Bible says will not inherit the Kingdom of God. I weep over this. Many will miss heaven because of this kind of ministry. Hear the Word of God - 1 Pet 4:17-18 For the time is come that judgment must begin at the house of God: and if it first begin at us, what shall the end be of them that obey not the gospel of God? And if the righteous scarcely be saved, where shall the ungodly and the sinner appear? Beloved, it is high time we did spiritual inventory of our own lives. Let's measure how we live by the Word of God. How do we measure up? Are we among the obedient or the disobedient? The first has blessings on them, the second has the wrath of God on them! Those of us who minister, are we telling it just like it is or are we trying to please men instead of God? Meditate on it!
Prayer
Father God, Forgive us when we fail to tell others the fullness of Your Word. May Your Word become the light to our path and the lamp to our feet so we never stumble in the dark. We ask, believe we receive, and give thanks in the Name of Jesus Christ. Amen.
